						<summary>

						<p>On one side of the doorway leading to the central shrine of the Gōliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Chāḷukya: Sarvalōkāśraya Vishṇuvardhana.</p>						

						<p>This is dated 25th year, Vishuva saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the grant of land to the temple of Bejayīśvara-Mahādēva. Mentions Padmaśiva, who received (the land) as <hi rend="italic">bhikshāvṛitti.</hi> In characters of 8th-9th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
